## **✈️ ABOUT THIS DOCUMENT**

See `main.pdf` for the tutorial on how to use the VICON positioning system with a Pixhawk6C.  
This document was originally aimed at AVDC MSc students at Cranfield for their GDP project,  
but I will also release it to the ArduPilot forum after receiving feedback that it is useful.

---

## **⚠️ DISCLAIMER**

This document is intentionally concise so you can get your drone connected to Vicon quickly.  
There are many ways to interface with Vicon (including writing your own SDK), but for your  
project this method is more than sufficient.

---

## **✒️ EDITING**

If you find a typo or a section that could be explained better, please fork this repository  
and submit a pull request.

This document is written in **LaTeX**.  
- Edit the main file: `main.tex`  
- Bibliography: `bibliography.bib`  
- Images: `Images/` folder

